THE INTERNATIONAL INFORMATION REPORT via NewsNet
JANUARY, 1996

BUILDING PEACE AND DEMOCRACY IN AFRICA

Two new reports by the U.S. Institute of Peace focus on efforts to 
build peace and democracy in Africa.
 
AFRICAN CONFLICT RESOLUTION:  THE U.S. ROLE IN PEACEMAKING, 192 
pages, $14.95, assesses various ways to improve the U.S. contribution 
to African efforts to prevent, manage, and resolve violent conflicts.
 
STATE BUILDING AND DEMOCRACY IN SOUTHERN AFRICA, 400 pages, $19.95, 
examines Botswana, Zimbabwe, and South Africa-three countries which 
each have different track records in establishing conditions in which 
democracy can grow.
 
Both books are available from the U.S. Institute of Peace Press, P.O. 
Box 605, Herndon, VA  22070, 800-868-9064; fax 703-689-0660.



