Foreigners net buyers of domestic demand stock in '95+

TOKYO, Dec. 28 Kyodo

     Foreign investors in Japan tended to be net buyers of domestic
demand-related shares and net sellers of high-tech-related shares in
1995, figures released Thursday by major brokerage companies showed.
     The following are the top 10 shares that met with net purchases
from foreigners, with stock volumes in millions.  The figures for
Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp. (NTT) were calculated on the
basis of each share having a face value of 50 yen.
 *
     1  NKK (135.05)
     2  Tokyo Electric Power (121.78)
     3  NTT (116.08)
     4  Sumitomo Metal Industries (120.20)
     5  Nippon Steel (101.20)
     6  Sony (92.34)
     7  Tokyo Steel Manufacturing (75.36)
     8  Hitachi (63.45)
     9  Mitsubishi Heavy Industries (61.15)
 10  Kobe Steel (59.69)
     The following are the top 10 shares that met with net selling
from foreigners.
     1  Toshiba (58.39)
