Fisherman sentenced to 6.5-year jail term over gun trade+

SHIZUOKA, Japan, Dec. 25 Kyodo

     A Japanese fisherman was sentenced to six and a half years in
jail at the Shizuoka District Court on Monday for masterminding
large-scale gun smuggling from South Africa for supply to crime
syndicates.
     Prosecutors had sought an eight-year prison term.
     Presiding Judge Katsutoshi Suzuki said in his ruling that
Hideaki Soga, 27, of Kagoshima, who worked aboard a tuna trawler,
