September 20, 1996

Samsung Electronics Floats $150 Million in CBs in London

from THE KOREA ECONOMIC DAILY, September 20, 1996

FINANCE

Samsung Electronics Co. (SEC) successfully floated $150 million worth
of overseas convertible bonds (CBs) in London.

The nation's No.1 semiconductor manufacturer said that it had a
signing ceremony to issue $150 million worth of CBs in London on
September 20 with Samsung Securities Co. and SBC Warburg acting as
managing underwriters.

The CBs carry a coupon rate of 0.25 percent, and yield to put (YTP) of
5.8 percent.

Conversion premium was fixed at 25 percent. Given that most overseas
depository receipts (DRs) traded in the international markets have a
premium of 10 to 15 percent, SEC CBs' conversion premium is offered
under more favorable conditions.

Copyright 1996 The Korea Economic Daily




