Toyota, Nissan in talks for tie-up in forklifts: daily+

TOKYO, Jan. 1 Kyodo

     Japan's ''Big Two'' automakers, Toyota Motor Corp. and Nissan
Motor Co., are in negotiations to enter into a tie-up in the area of
forklifts in North America, an industrial daily reported Monday.
     The Nikkan Kogyo Shimbun quoted sources familiar with the talks
as saying the two auto giants plan to supply each other with key
components of forklifts to be turned out in the United States.
