Canon to boost annual stepper output 60%, daily says+

TOKYO, Jan. 1 Kyodo

     Major precision instrument maker Canon Inc. is to increase its
annual production capacity of steppers for use in manufacturing
semiconductors for fiscal 1996 by 60% from the current fiscal year
to 800 units, a business daily said Monday.
     The Nihon Keizai Shimbun said the Tokyo-based company will soon
begin construction of a new factory in Utsunomiya, Tochigi
Prefecture, north of Tokyo, to start operations around this summer.
     Construction costs are estimated at 5 billion to 6 billion yen,
