     With the new plant, Canon intends to catch up with Nikon Corp.,
the stepper industry leader that holds 50% of the world's stepper
market compared with about 40% for Canon.
     Nikon also plans to raise its annual stepper output capacity by
65% during fiscal 1996 which starts in April.
     The production increases by Nikon and Canon are in response to
strong demand from semiconductor manufacturers.



