the prosecution of those involved in the military crackdown of the
1980 civilian uprising in the southern city of Kwangju that claimed
at least 192 lives.
     Kim was elected in December 1992 as the first president with no
military background in more than 30 years.
     The South Korean leader also said he hopes the new year will be
one of hope and joy for North Korean people who are suffering many
difficulties.



