     Military intelligence had arrested 40 army officers in
Rawalpindi last September for allegedly plotting the elimination of
military and political leaders, and to then declare an Islamic state
in Pakistan.
     While some of the detainees have been released, others have
turned witness and only four of the main suspects accused have been
formally charged by military authorities.
     The Public Relations Department of the Pakistani army has not
given out any details about the start of the trial for the arrested
army officers.
     Several politicians and retired military officers have demanded
an open trial for the accused but that has been rejected by the
government.



