vacation of two months over fears Tamil separatists might target such
facilities, especially in the capital of Colombo.
     -- Emperor Akihito said in a speech at a New Year's celebration
at the Imperial Palace that he hopes it will be a better year with
national development and happiness for all Japanese.
     -- Scandal-tainted Daiwa Bank plans to enter into plea-bargaining
as early as next month with U.S. federal law-enforcement authorities
over 24 counts of criminal fraud filed against it, a national daily
reported.
     -- Major precision instrument maker Canon Inc. is to increase
its annual production capacity of steppers for use in manufacturing
semiconductors for fiscal 1996 by 60% from the current fiscal
year to 800 units, a business daily said.
     -- Four Japanese nationals have been selected as sacred flame
runners for the Atlanta Olympic Games in July.
     -- At least four people were killed and more than 700 others
injured, mostly from powerful firecrackers or gunshots, in the
Philippines during New Year's revelry, health officials said.



